  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;Puppets against-abuse&quot; in Kinshasa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Kinshasa, there are an estimated 20,000 children living in the streets. Many of them have become outcasts, having been accused of witchcraft. Puppeteers Without Borders give local educators, artists/puppeteers the tools to address this specific problem through puppetry and training; puppet performances promote new understandings that can lead to behavioural changes; education and training provide teachers with powerful tools with which to facilitate healing.</narrative>
  </description>
